Hackathon-Citi-MongoDB-DBconfigSteps

cd to C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\3.2\bin>
C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\8.0\bin
enter command mongod
by default, mongodb server will start at port 27017


Start MongoDB locally or via a service like MongoDB Atlas.
Database name: pdfEditorDb
Collection name: pdfFields


mongod --dbpath <path-to-your-data-directory>
Replace <path-to-your-data-directory> with the path where you want MongoDB to store its data.


mongod --dbpath C:\Users\usudi\Downloads\Hackathon-Citi\MongoOutput

After momgo db install

Add to PATH:

Press Win + R, type sysdm.cpl, and press Enter.
Go to the Advanced tab and click Environment Variables.
Under System Variables, find Path, select it, and click Edit.
Click New, and add the full path to MongoDB's bin directory (e.g., C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\6.0\bin).
Click OK to save